\par\plain \f0\fs22\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs22\b0\i0 The perfect equality of the Holy Spirit's perception is the counterpart of the perfect equality of God's knowing.}
\par\plain \f0\fs22\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs22\b0\i0 the Holy Spirit remains the bridge between perception and knowledge.}
\par\plain \f0\fs22\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs22\b0\i0 By enabling you to use perception in a way that PARALLELS knowledge, you will ultimately meet it and KNOW it.}
\par\plain \f0\fs22\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs22\b0\i0 He can INSPIRE perception and lead it toward God by making it PARALLEL to God's way of thinking}
\par\plain \f0\fs22\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs22\b0\i0 This is the way in which you MUST perceive God's Creations, bringing all of your perceptions into the one parallel line which the Holy Spirit sees.}
\par\plain \f0\fs22\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs22\b0\i0 There is no conflict anywhere in this PERCEPTION, because it means that ALL PERCEPTION is guided by the Holy Spirit, whose mind is fixed on God. ONLY the Holy Spirit can resolve conflict, because ONLY the Holy Spirit is conflict-free. HE PERCEIVES ONLY WHAT IS TRUE IN YOUR MIND, and extends outward to ONLY what is true in other minds. }
\par\plain \f0\fs22\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs22\b0\i0 We have repeatedly emphasized the fact that one level of the mind is not understandable to another. So it is with the ego and the soul, and with time and eternity.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs22\b0\i0 Me: Levels of reality in the UB? }
\par\plain {\f0\fs18\b0\i0\cf3 (196:3.10)}{\f0\fs22\b0\i0  The human mind does not create real values; human experience does not yield universe insight. Concerning insight, the recognition of moral values and the discernment of spiritual meanings, all that the human mind can do is to discover, recognize, interpret, and }{\f1\fs22\b0\i1 choose.}
\par\plain \f1\fs22\b0\i1
\par\plain {\f0\fs22\b0\i0 When the Holy Spirit has at last led you to Christ, at the altar to His Father, PERCEPTION FUSES INTO KNOWLEDGE, because perception has become so holy that its transfer to Holiness is merely its natural extension.}
\par\plain \f0\fs22\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs22\b0\i0 At the altar of God, the holy PERCEPTION of God's Son becomes so enlightened that light streams into it}
\par\plain \f0\fs22\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs22\b0\i0 Life and death, light and darkness, knowledge and perception are irreconcilable.}
\par\plain \f0\fs22\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs22\b0\i0 Everyone can use his body best by enlarging man's perception, so he can see the real VISION. THIS VISION is invisible to the physical eye.}
\par\plain \f0\fs22\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs22\b0\i0 Readiness here means keep your perception right side up, (or valid), so you will ALWAYS be ready, willing, and able.}
\par\plain \f0\fs22\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs22\b0\i0 And all perception can be given a new purpose by the One Whom God appointed Savior to the world.}
\par\plain \f0\fs22\b0\i0
\par\plain {\f0\fs22\b0\i0 Perfect perception can merely show you what is CAPABLE of being wholly shared. \tab }
